spec: uuid_extra105
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(uuid)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/uuid.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/uuid.html — Python uuid module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/uuid.py"
    - "uuid_extra104.zspec.zsdl — covers UUID class __name__/__module__/__qualname__ equality and lengths / UUID property fget qualname lengths / uuid.getnode identity and NAMESPACE str lengths (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra103.zspec.zsdl — covers uuid1/uuid3/uuid4/uuid5 __module__ equality / uuid module __name__/__package__/__spec__ identity / UUID.__new__ qualname 'object.__new__' (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra102.zspec.zsdl — covers UUID.variant property vs UUID.is_safe member_descriptor / UUID.__reduce__/__hash__/__str__ type and qualname / UUID comparison method qualnames (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra101.zspec.zsdl — covers SafeUUID enum class identity (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra100.zspec.zsdl — covers UUID class-level descriptor types and __slots__ (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra99.zspec.zsdl — covers UUID.__str__/__repr__ qualname equality and lengths / UUID.__eq__/__hash__/__lt__ qualname equality and lengths / UUID.__init__ code attributes (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra97.zspec.zsdl — covers UUID property fget qualname string equality / type(UUID.hex).__name__=='property' (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra96.zspec.zsdl — covers uuid1/uuid3/uuid4/uuid5 __code__.co_name / UUID.__module__/__class__/__qualname__ equality and length (table + invariants)."
    - "uuid_extra86.zspec.zsdl — covers UUID.__init__/__code__/co_name/co_argcount/__qualname__ / uuid1/uuid4/uuid3/uuid5/getnode __qualname__/__module__/co_argcount (table + invariants)."
  notes:
    - "This spec extends uuid through uuid_extra104; it does NOT duplicate invariants present in those files."
    - "Wave 273 theme: UUID comparison operator method qualnames not yet covered (__le__, __gt__, __ge__) / UUID.__int__ qualname and co_argcount / UUID method co_argcount grouping for unary vs binary methods."
    - "uuid.UUID.__le__.__qualname__ == 'UUID.__le__' (11 chars). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__gt__.__qualname__ == 'UUID.__gt__' (11 chars). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__ge__.__qualname__ == 'UUID.__ge__' (11 chars). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__int__.__qualname__ == 'UUID.__int__' (12 chars). Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__le__.__class__.__name__ == 'function'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__gt__.__class__.__name__ == 'function'. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__str__.__code__.co_argcount == 1. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__repr__.__code__.co_argcount == 1. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__hash__.__code__.co_argcount == 1. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__int__.__code__.co_argcount == 1. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__eq__.__code__.co_argcount == 2. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "uuid.UUID.__lt__.__code__.co_argcount == 2. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "str(uuid.NAMESPACE_OID).__len__() == 36. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "str(uuid.NAMESPACE_X500).__len__() == 36. Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0."
    - "Note: UUID.__le__, UUID.__gt__, UUID.__ge__ are Python 'function' objects (defined in Lib/uuid.py) with qualnames 'UUID.__le__', 'UUID.__gt__', 'UUID.__ge__' — all 11 chars (same as UUID.__eq__ and UUID.__lt__ which were covered in uuid_extra99). uuid_extra99 anchored __eq__/__lt__ qualnames; this spec anchors the remaining comparison operators __le__/__gt__/__ge__ for the first time."
    - "Note: UUID.__int__ is a Python function with qualname 'UUID.__int__' (12 chars: 'UUID.'=5 + '__int__'=7). It returns the UUID as a 128-bit integer (the .int attribute). co_argcount==1 (self only). uuid_extra100 anchors UUID.int as member_descriptor; uuid_extra96 anchors UUID.__module__; this spec anchors UUID.__int__ method identity for the first time."
    - "Note: co_argcount grouping — unary methods (self only, co_argcount==1): __str__, __repr__, __hash__, __int__. Binary methods (self + other, co_argcount==2): __eq__, __lt__, __le__, __gt__, __ge__. uuid_extra99 anchors UUID.__init__ co_argcount==7; this spec anchors the unary/binary pattern for other UUID methods."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid.UUID.__le__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__le__')
# uuid.UUID.__gt__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__gt__')
# uuid.UUID.__ge__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__ge__')
# uuid.UUID.__le__.__qualname__.__len__() == 11
# uuid.UUID.__int__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__int__')
#
# Wave 273 theme: UUID comparison operator and conversion method qualnames.
#
# UUID.__le__, UUID.__gt__, UUID.__ge__ are Python functions (not C methods) with
# qualnames 'UUID.__le__', 'UUID.__gt__', 'UUID.__ge__' (all 11 chars: 'UUID.'=5
# + 5-char dunder name). uuid_extra99 anchored __eq__ (11 chars) and __lt__ (11 chars);
# this spec anchors the remaining three comparison operators (__le__, __gt__, __ge__).
# UUID.__int__ has qualname 'UUID.__int__' (12 chars: 'UUID.'=5 + '__int__'=7).
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table uuid_extra105.UUID_comparison_and_int_method_qualnames:
  description: "UUID.__le__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__le__')==True / UUID.__gt__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__gt__')==True / UUID.__ge__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__ge__')==True / UUID.__le__.__qualname__.__len__()==11 / UUID.__int__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__int__')==True — __le__/__gt__/__ge__ all 11 chars (same as __eq__/__lt__ covered in extra99); __int__ is 12 chars ('UUID.'=5+'__int__'=7); all are Python functions; first uuidmeth105 anchor for __le__/__gt__/__ge__/__int__"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: method_identity
  id_prefix: uuidmeth105

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [le_qualname_eq,  "UUID.__le__.__qualname__.__eq__",  ["UUID.__le__"],  true, "uuid.UUID.__le__.__qualname__ is 'UUID.__le__' (11 chars; 'UUID.'=5 + '__le__'=6; less-than-or-equal comparison)"]
    - [gt_qualname_eq,  "UUID.__gt__.__qualname__.__eq__",  ["UUID.__gt__"],  true, "uuid.UUID.__gt__.__qualname__ is 'UUID.__gt__' (11 chars; 'UUID.'=5 + '__gt__'=6; greater-than comparison)"]
    - [ge_qualname_eq,  "UUID.__ge__.__qualname__.__eq__",  ["UUID.__ge__"],  true, "uuid.UUID.__ge__.__qualname__ is 'UUID.__ge__' (11 chars; 'UUID.'=5 + '__ge__'=6; greater-than-or-equal comparison)"]
    - [le_qualname_len, "UUID.__le__.__qualname__.__len__", [],               11,   "uuid.UUID.__le__.__qualname__.__len__() is 11 (same as UUID.__eq__ and UUID.__lt__ covered in extra99)"]
    - [int_qualname_eq, "UUID.__int__.__qualname__.__eq__", ["UUID.__int__"], true, "uuid.UUID.__int__.__qualname__ is 'UUID.__int__' (12 chars; 'UUID.'=5 + '__int__'=7; returns UUID as 128-bit int)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid.UUID.__str__.__code__.co_argcount == 1
# uuid.UUID.__repr__.__code__.co_argcount == 1
# uuid.UUID.__hash__.__code__.co_argcount == 1
# uuid.UUID.__int__.__code__.co_argcount == 1
# uuid.UUID.__eq__.__code__.co_argcount == 2
#
# Wave 273 theme: UUID method co_argcount grouping — unary vs binary.
#
# UUID methods divide into two co_argcount groups: unary methods (co_argcount==1,
# taking only self) and binary methods (co_argcount==2, taking self + other).
# Unary: __str__, __repr__, __hash__, __int__ all have co_argcount==1.
# Binary: __eq__, __lt__, __le__, __gt__, __ge__ all have co_argcount==2.
# uuid_extra86 anchors UUID.__init__ co_argcount==7; uuid_extra99 anchors
# UUID.__init__ co_argcount via __eq__ call. This spec anchors the unary/binary
# grouping for other UUID methods for the first time.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table uuid_extra105.UUID_method_co_argcount_grouping:
  description: "UUID.__str__.__code__.co_argcount==1 / UUID.__repr__.__code__.co_argcount==1 / UUID.__hash__.__code__.co_argcount==1 / UUID.__int__.__code__.co_argcount==1 / UUID.__eq__.__code__.co_argcount==2 — unary methods (self only): __str__, __repr__, __hash__, __int__ all have co_argcount==1; binary methods (self + other): __eq__/__lt__/__le__/__gt__/__ge__ have co_argcount==2; extra86 anchors UUID.__init__ co_argcount==7; first uuidmeth105 anchor for unary/binary grouping"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: code_attr
  id_prefix: uuidmeth105

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [str_co_argcount,    "UUID.__str__.__code__.co_argcount",    [], 1, "uuid.UUID.__str__.__code__.co_argcount is 1 (unary; takes only self; returns standard UUID string representation)"]
    - [repr_co_argcount,   "UUID.__repr__.__code__.co_argcount",   [], 1, "uuid.UUID.__repr__.__code__.co_argcount is 1 (unary; takes only self; returns 'UUID(...)' repr string)"]
    - [hash_co_argcount,   "UUID.__hash__.__code__.co_argcount",   [], 1, "uuid.UUID.__hash__.__code__.co_argcount is 1 (unary; takes only self; computes hash from the .int attribute)"]
    - [int_co_argcount,    "UUID.__int__.__code__.co_argcount",    [], 1, "uuid.UUID.__int__.__code__.co_argcount is 1 (unary; takes only self; returns UUID as 128-bit integer)"]
    - [eq_co_argcount,     "UUID.__eq__.__code__.co_argcount",     [], 2, "uuid.UUID.__eq__.__code__.co_argcount is 2 (binary; takes self + other; compares by .int value)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid.UUID.__le__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function')
# uuid.UUID.__gt__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function')
# uuid.UUID.__ge__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function')
# str(uuid.NAMESPACE_OID).__len__() == 36
# str(uuid.NAMESPACE_X500).__len__() == 36
#
# Wave 273 theme: UUID comparison operator types and NAMESPACE constant string lengths.
#
# UUID.__le__, UUID.__gt__, UUID.__ge__ are Python 'function' objects (defined in
# Lib/uuid.py), not C methods. uuid_extra99 notes that UUID.__str__, UUID.__eq__,
# UUID.__hash__ are type 'function'; this spec extends the type identity check to
# __le__, __gt__, __ge__. NAMESPACE_OID and NAMESPACE_X500 (like NAMESPACE_DNS
# and NAMESPACE_URL covered in uuid_extra104) have 36-char str() representations.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table uuid_extra105.UUID_comparison_method_types_and_namespace_lengths:
  description: "UUID.__le__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function')==True / UUID.__gt__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function')==True / UUID.__ge__.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function')==True / str(NAMESPACE_OID).__len__()==36 / str(NAMESPACE_X500).__len__()==36 — __le__/__gt__/__ge__ are Python functions (not C methods; defined in Lib/uuid.py); NAMESPACE_OID and NAMESPACE_X500 str() have 36 chars (same as NAMESPACE_DNS/URL from extra104; all UUID strings are 36 chars); first uuidmeth105 anchor for these"
  kind: python_call_eq
  category: method_identity
  id_prefix: uuidmeth105

  columns: [id, function, args, expected, description]
  rows:
    - [le_type_eq,          "UUID.__le__.__class__.__name__.__eq__",   ["function"], true, "uuid.UUID.__le__ is a Python function (defined in Lib/uuid.py; not a C builtin_function_or_method)"]
    - [gt_type_eq,          "UUID.__gt__.__class__.__name__.__eq__",   ["function"], true, "uuid.UUID.__gt__ is a Python function (defined in Lib/uuid.py; provides greater-than comparison for UUID sorting)"]
    - [ge_type_eq,          "UUID.__ge__.__class__.__name__.__eq__",   ["function"], true, "uuid.UUID.__ge__ is a Python function (defined in Lib/uuid.py; provides greater-than-or-equal comparison)"]
    - [ns_oid_str_len,      "NAMESPACE_OID.__str__().__len__",         [],           36,   "str(uuid.NAMESPACE_OID).__len__() is 36 (standard UUID string: 8-4-4-4-12 hex groups with 4 hyphens)"]
    - [ns_x500_str_len,     "NAMESPACE_X500.__str__().__len__",        [],           36,   "str(uuid.NAMESPACE_X500).__len__() is 36 (all UUID instances have 36-char str(); same as NAMESPACE_DNS/URL from extra104)"]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid.UUID.__le__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__le__') — standalone
#
# uuid.UUID.__le__.__qualname__ is 'UUID.__le__' (11 chars: 'UUID.'=5 + '__le__'=6).
# __le__ implements the <= comparison operator for UUID. uuid_extra99 anchored
# __eq__ (11 chars) and __lt__ (11 chars) qualnames; __le__ has the same length
# (11 chars) as both of those. UUID comparison methods are implemented using the
# UUID .int attribute (a 128-bit integer), so __le__ compares two UUIDs by
# comparing their integer values. No prior uuid spec anchors __le__ qualname.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant uuid_extra105.UUID_le_qualname_eq:
  description: "uuid.UUID.__le__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__le__') == True — qualname is 'UUID.__le__' (11 chars; 'UUID.'=5 + '__le__'=6; same length as UUID.__eq__ and UUID.__lt__ from extra99); implements <= operator by comparing .int values; extra99 anchored __eq__/__lt__ qualnames; first standalone for __le__ under uuidmeth105"
  category: method_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "UUID.__le__.__qualname__.__eq__"
  args: ["UUID.__le__"]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid.UUID.__gt__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__gt__') — standalone
#
# uuid.UUID.__gt__.__qualname__ is 'UUID.__gt__' (11 chars: 'UUID.'=5 + '__gt__'=6).
# __gt__ implements the > comparison operator. All five UUID comparison operators
# (__eq__, __lt__, __le__, __gt__, __ge__) have qualnames of length 11 chars.
# This is because all their dunder names are 6 chars: __eq__, __lt__, __le__,
# __gt__, __ge__ — all are 3-letter operator codes wrapped in double underscores
# (6 chars total). uuid_extra99 anchors __eq__ and __lt__; this spec anchors __gt__.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant uuid_extra105.UUID_gt_qualname_eq:
  description: "uuid.UUID.__gt__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__gt__') == True — qualname is 'UUID.__gt__' (11 chars; 'UUID.'=5 + '__gt__'=6); all five UUID comparison operators have qualname length 11 (dunder names are all 6 chars: 3-letter op code + double underscores on each side); extra99 anchors __eq__/__lt__; first standalone for __gt__ under uuidmeth105"
  category: method_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "UUID.__gt__.__qualname__.__eq__"
  args: ["UUID.__gt__"]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid.UUID.__int__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__int__') — standalone
#
# uuid.UUID.__int__.__qualname__ is 'UUID.__int__' (12 chars: 'UUID.'=5 +
# '__int__'=7). UUID.__int__ returns the UUID as a 128-bit integer (the .int
# attribute). The qualname 'UUID.__int__' is 12 chars — one more than the 5-char
# comparison operators (__eq__, __lt__, etc. at 11 chars) because '__int__' is
# 7 chars (3-letter type code 'int' wrapped in double underscores). No prior uuid
# spec anchors UUID.__int__ qualname as a standalone.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant uuid_extra105.UUID_int_qualname_eq:
  description: "uuid.UUID.__int__.__qualname__.__eq__('UUID.__int__') == True — qualname is 'UUID.__int__' (12 chars; 'UUID.'=5 + '__int__'=7); 12 chars because '__int__' is 7 chars (3-letter type code 'int' wrapped in double underscores vs 6-char comparison dunder names); returns UUID as 128-bit integer; first standalone under uuidmeth105"
  category: method_identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "UUID.__int__.__qualname__.__eq__"
  args: ["UUID.__int__"]
  expected: true

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid.UUID.__str__.__code__.co_argcount == 1 — standalone
#
# uuid.UUID.__str__.__code__.co_argcount is 1. UUID.__str__ is a Python function
# (type 'function') that takes only 'self' as argument. co_argcount==1 is the
# minimum for a method (any method must accept at least self). uuid_extra99
# confirms UUID.__str__ type is 'function' and anchors its qualname equality
# and length. uuid_extra86 anchors UUID.__init__ co_argcount==7. This spec
# anchors UUID.__str__ co_argcount==1 as a standalone for the first time.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant uuid_extra105.UUID_str_co_argcount:
  description: "uuid.UUID.__str__.__code__.co_argcount == 1 — unary method taking only self; minimum co_argcount for any method; UUID.__str__ returns standard 36-char hyphenated UUID string; extra99 anchors __str__ qualname and type; extra86 anchors __init__ co_argcount==7; first standalone for __str__ co_argcount under uuidmeth105"
  category: code_attr
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "UUID.__str__.__code__.co_argcount"
  args: []
  expected: 1

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# uuid.UUID.__eq__.__code__.co_argcount == 2 — standalone
#
# uuid.UUID.__eq__.__code__.co_argcount is 2. UUID.__eq__ takes self (the UUID
# being compared) and other (the object to compare against). co_argcount==2
# is the signature of all binary comparison methods (__eq__, __lt__, __le__,
# __gt__, __ge__). UUID.__eq__ compares by the .int attribute (a 128-bit integer),
# returning True only when both UUIDs have the same int value. uuid_extra99
# anchors UUID.__eq__ qualname equality; this spec anchors its co_argcount.
# Verified Python 3.14.3 macOS/Darwin 25.4.0.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

invariant uuid_extra105.UUID_eq_co_argcount:
  description: "uuid.UUID.__eq__.__code__.co_argcount == 2 — binary method taking self + other; co_argcount==2 for all five UUID comparison operators (__eq__, __lt__, __le__, __gt__, __ge__); UUID.__eq__ compares .int values (128-bit integer comparison); extra99 anchors UUID.__eq__ qualname; first standalone for __eq__ co_argcount under uuidmeth105"
  category: code_attr
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "UUID.__eq__.__code__.co_argcount"
  args: []
  expected: 2
